author: Mudae
content:
**info flags**: Add those letters to some commands ($mm, $ima...) to display different informations:
**w** (waifu), **h** (husbando), **wh** (both genders), **w=** (waifu without both genders), **h=** (husbando without both genders)
**g** (game), **g-** (animanga), **gg-** (both), **g=** (game only), **g-=** (animanga only)
**a** (series list), **a+** (series names), **b** (series bundles), **p** (character search if you type some text), **s** (DM)

**e** (tags), **e=** (sort by number of tags)
**r** (claim ranks), **r-** (claim ranks not sorted), **l** (like ranks), **l-** (like ranks not sorted)
**k** (kakera value), **k=** (kakera sorted), **k-** (value without keys)
**y** (keys only), **y=** (keys sorted), **y+** (with full harem), **y-** (without keys)
Equivalent for soulkeys: **y!**, **y!=**, **y!+**, **y!-**
**c** (embedcolored), **c+** (with full harem), **c-** (without embedcolor)

**t** (type of rolls), **m** (main names), **d** (img/alias/series details), **v** (hide details such as notes), **n** (not noted), **n+** (noted only)
**u** (unclaimed), **o** (owner names), **o=** (owned only), **o-** (not owned by you), **o+** (owned by you)
**o!** (flags are about you when checking another user)
**x** (disabled), **x+** (with full harem), **x-** (not disabled)
**q!** (inexact search), **q=** (exact search), **q+** (exact start), **q-** (exact end), **==** (alphabetical sort)
**i** (images), **i-** (hide images if DM)

**Available arguments** (type a space after the command, don't type the <>):
<**series name**>, <**page**>, <**@User, User ID or User tag**>, $mm serv <server ID>
Add **--** in front of a series, character, tag or note to exclude it from the search.
For multiple arguments, separate them with a **$**

__Example:__ *$mmwr Re:Zero*
__**SLASH COMMANDS** Example:__ */mm /wr Re:Zero*

author: Mudae
content:
Syntax: **$ima** <series to search>

Type **$s flags** for the list of filters.

**$imaq!** <series> if you want to return the list instead of one series.
**$ima** <series 1>$<series 2> for multiple series.
**$ima** <series>$<page> to jump to the page.
**$imab** <series> for the bundle list of the series.
**$imap** <series> = <character(s)> to search by character name.
**$imae** <series> = <tag(s)> to search by tag.
**$ima&** <bundle 1>$<bundle 2> to not search by series overlapping.
**$imaq+** <series> (or $imaq- <series>) to only search for series containing a part starting (or ending) exactly by your request.
**$ima?** <series> to display all aliases, including those from other countries, and the definition if available.
**$ima*** to only display characters whose main series is this one.
**$ima*-** to only display characters whose main series is not this one.
**$ima*+** to display characters regardless of their main series (useful for bundles).

Ex.: $imawo attack on titan

author: Mudae
content:
**info flags**: Add those letters to some commands ($mm, $ima...) to display different informations:
**w** (waifu), **h** (husbando), **wh** (both genders), **w=** (waifu without both genders), **h=** (husbando without both genders)
**g** (game), **g-** (animanga), **gg-** (both), **g=** (game only), **g-=** (animanga only)
**a** (series list), **a+** (series names), **b** (series bundles), **p** (character search if you type some text), **s** (DM)

**e** (tags), **e=** (sort by number of tags)
**r** (claim ranks), **r-** (claim ranks not sorted), **l** (like ranks), **l-** (like ranks not sorted)
**k** (kakera value), **k=** (kakera sorted), **k-** (value without keys)
**y** (keys only), **y=** (keys sorted), **y+** (with full harem), **y-** (without keys)
Equivalent for soulkeys: **y!**, **y!=**, **y!+**, **y!-**
**c** (embedcolored), **c+** (with full harem), **c-** (without embedcolor)

**t** (type of rolls), **m** (main names), **d** (img/alias/series details), **v** (hide details such as notes), **n** (not noted), **n+** (noted only)
**u** (unclaimed), **o** (owner names), **o=** (owned only), **o-** (not owned by you), **o+** (owned by you)
**o!** (flags are about you when checking another user)
**x** (disabled), **x+** (with full harem), **x-** (not disabled)
**q!** (inexact search), **q=** (exact search), **q+** (exact start), **q-** (exact end), **==** (alphabetical sort)
**i** (images), **i-** (hide images if DM)

**Available arguments** (type a space after the command, don't type the <>):
<**series name**>, <**page**>, <**@User, User ID or User tag**>, $mm serv <server ID>
Add **--** in front of a series, character, tag or note to exclude it from the search.
For multiple arguments, separate them with a **$**

__Example:__ *$mmwr Re:Zero*
__**SLASH COMMANDS** Example:__ */mm /wr Re:Zero*

author: Mudae
content:
**$topserv**: ($ts) Server ladder for the sum of the 15 highest ranked characters by claims.
**$topservl**: ($tsl) Server ladder for the sum of the 15 highest ranked characters by likes.
**$topservv**: ($tsv) Server ladder for the harem kakera value. Use `$tsv id` to display user IDs.
**$topservk**: ($tsk) Server ladder for total kakera. Use `$tsk id` to display user IDs.
**$topservy**: ($tsy) Server ladder for characters with the most of keys. Use `$tsy id` to display user IDs.
**$topservyb**: ($tsyb) Server ladder for users with the best key level per character.
**$topservyt**: ($tsyt) Server ladder for users with the highest amount of keys.
**$topserv nbr**: ($ts nbr) Server ladder for the number of claimed characters.
**$topserv lastclaim**: ($ts lc) Date of the last claim for each user.
**$top**: Ladder of characters by ranks. See `$s flags`

author: Mudae
content:
Syntax: **$ima** <series to search>

Type **$s flags** for the list of filters.

**$imaq!** <series> if you want to return the list instead of one series.
**$ima** <series 1>$<series 2> for multiple series.
**$ima** <series>$<page> to jump to the page.
**$imab** <series> for the bundle list of the series.
**$imap** <series> = <character(s)> to search by character name.
**$imae** <series> = <tag(s)> to search by tag.
**$ima&** <bundle 1>$<bundle 2> to not search by series overlapping.
**$imaq+** <series> (or $imaq- <series>) to only search for series containing a part starting (or ending) exactly by your request.
**$ima?** <series> to display all aliases, including those from other countries, and the definition if available.
**$ima*** to only display characters whose main series is this one.
**$ima*-** to only display characters whose main series is not this one.
**$ima*+** to display characters regardless of their main series (useful for bundles).

Ex.: $imawo attack on titan

author: Mudae
content:
1/17 - Tutorial
This tutorial will guide you through the main features of Mudae.
To change the language (fr, pt-br or es), type **$lang** (admin command).
if you have already done this tutorial on another server, you can skip and get the rewards with **$skiptuto**


<:did:990886355028553798> **COLLECT YOUR FIRST CHARACTER**
Type $w to spawn a random waifu or $h for a random husbando. This is called a roll.
To collect (claim) a character, quickly add a reaction to the roll.
By default you have 30 seconds to react and you can claim one character every 3 hours.
You can add the letter g ($wg, $hg) to only spawn video game characters, or the letter a ($wa, $ha) to not spawn video game specific characters.
Use $m (or $ma, $mg) if you don't have a gender preference.


<:do:990886344542797845> **CHECK YOUR COLLECTED CHARACTERS**
Type $mm to see your list of claimed characters.
A character can only be owned by one person in each server.
This list is not global: it is bound to this server only.


**Reward: 200<:kakera:469835869059153940>**

author: Mudae
content:
Syntax: **$ima** <series to search>

Type **$s flags** for the list of filters.

**$imaq!** <series> if you want to return the list instead of one series.
**$ima** <series 1>$<series 2> for multiple series.
**$ima** <series>$<page> to jump to the page.
**$imab** <series> for the bundle list of the series.
**$imap** <series> = <character(s)> to search by character name.
**$imae** <series> = <tag(s)> to search by tag.
**$ima&** <bundle 1>$<bundle 2> to not search by series overlapping.
**$imaq+** <series> (or $imaq- <series>) to only search for series containing a part starting (or ending) exactly by your request.
**$ima?** <series> to display all aliases, including those from other countries, and the definition if available.
**$ima*** to only display characters whose main series is this one.
**$ima*-** to only display characters whose main series is not this one.
**$ima*+** to display characters regardless of their main series (useful for bundles).

Ex.: $imawo attack on titan
